headline: The Bull Case For Vulcan Materials (VMC) Could Change Following Robust Q3 Results and Upbeat Outlook
summary: Vulcan Materials recently reported strong third-quarter results, with revenue rising 14.4% year over year and adjusted EBITDA up 26.5%, while management reaffirmed full-year guidance for adjusted EBITDA in the range of US$2.35 billion to US$2.45 billion. Analysts highlighted Vulcan’s consistent margin expansion and operational efficiency, pointing to expanding opportunities for capital deployment and unit profitability as key drivers for future performance.
